<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>The __call method, trying to describe an occured error, uses a hard-coded, own implementation</p>

<p>Zend/Controller/Action.php, line 483
[code]
  if ('Action' == substr($methodName, -6)) {
[/code]</p>

<p>to detect if the user tried to call an (non existing) action or method.
If a user does not rely on Zend_Controller_Dispatcher_Abstract's formatActionName() but uses his onw dispatcher, the exception thrown is misleading, as indicating call to an action where a method was called and vice-versa.</p>

